5:
Tch, they just keep coming! How you
holding up?
8:
I'm okay, but I don't know how many
more of these I can handle!
11:
That's right! Keep it up! Fight them
off with everything ya got!
13:
Second battalion, reporting in! Hurry,
take the injured to the rear!
16: Wow... These guys know how to fight.
19:
No kidding. I thought we were done
for back there...
23: Nngh... Not yet! We can still—
24:
Hehe, you've done your part. Rest
now.
34:
Well done, everyone. Thank you for
securing the frontline.
37:
From this point on, I, Mamnalia, shall
assume command of the
advancing squadrons. Now who's
with me?
44:
Wait, so she single-handedly won
the battle on the other boats too?
47:
Indeed she did. I was only there for
the tail end of the scuffle, but from
what I saw, her magic and rallying
cry completely turned the tides.
55:
Excuse me... Could I ask for a
moment of your time?
58:
You are the mercenaries we hired
for this battle, correct? You have my
gratitude for supporting our troops.
62:
I am Mamnalia, a master in healing
arts and head of the Float that hired
you. Are you all unharmed?
66:
Ah, yeah, we're fine. Your magic
healed us up!
70:
Hehe, you're a strong one, aren't
you? The soldiers on your boat sang
your praises, you know. They said
you really helped them out.
75: Good... I see no debilitating injuries.
79:
Are you taking care of all these
people alone?
82:
Not exactly. My students are helping
me perform my duties.
87:
Um... Is there anything we can do to
help?
91:
Oh my, what a sweet boy you are. In
that case, I suppose I could find
something for you to do.
95:
There, all finished. You certainly did
a number on your body. No more
overexerting yourself, understand?
98:
Urgh... I'm sorry, but there's
something I must—
101:
I am eternally grateful for your
dedication and service up until this
point. You did well.
104:
Which is why it pains me to see you
make light of your own health. If you
will not rest for your own sake... will
you at least do so for mine?
108:
That was amazing... You knew just
what to say to calm him down...
111:
Hehe, thank you. But I'm only doing
what I can.
114:
I still have a long ways to go before
I'll be able to help people the world
over.
122:
That's right. You would know
something about that, wouldn't you?
Crimson Blades.
130:
Yes... I've actually been looking
forward to the day we could finally
meet.
132:
Your method of helping others
allows you to save those I cannot.
136:
I just don't know HOW you do it. So I
believe there is much I can learn
from you.
143:
What? How?! We already defeated
so many of them...
147:
Stella, stand back! Alk, please
protect the injured!
162:
Mm... Huh? We're back home... What
happened?
166: Idiot! Don't scare us like that!
170:
Alk, you probably don't recall this,
but you were poisoned by a
monster.
174:
Fortunately for you, the World Flipper
was close by. I apologize, Lady
Mamnalia... We dragged you here
without any explanation.
178:
No, that's all right. I'm happy to know
you trust me enough to reveal this
place to me.
182:
So that's what happened... Thank
you for helping me, Mamnalia.
189:
Oh, she's fine. She and I just had a
nice long chat... And I do believe you
need a good talking to as well.
193:
Alk... Rushing into a situation where
you KNOW you are at a
disadvantage is nothing short of
foolhardiness.
200:
And if you think you are doing this
for the sake of others... How do you
think it feels to watch someone
throw their life away for you?
204:
I... I promise that's not what I was
trying to do. I just jumped in without
thinking.
208:
Is that so? Well, if that's really what
happened...
210:
Then I am even more certain that I
have much to learn from you.
218:
I also wish to oversee your recovery.
Would it be all right if I stayed here
while I observe my patient?
223:
You'd be doing us a service if you
did, but... Is that all right with you,
Stella?
228:
Of course. Welcome to Starview
Village, Mamnalia.
233:
Thank you. In that case, I should
send word to my people as well.
237: I look forward to working with you all.
